    "class OrderBook(object):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, ob_data):\n",
    "        '''This class represents an order book at any point in time.  The time stamp of the orderbok is saved as an instance property'''\n",
    "        data_list = []\n",
    "        for ii in ob_data[1].items():\n",
    "            data_list.append((ii[0],ii[1][0], ii[1][1]))\n",
    "            \n",
    "        df = pd.DataFrame.from_records(data_list, columns=[\"P\",\"Q\",\"S\"])\n",
    "        self.timestamp = ob_data[0]\n",
    "        df = df.sort_values(by=[\"P\"])\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Now make the orderbook cumulative.\n",
    "        #Bid side first\n",
    "        df_bids = df[df['S'] == \"B\"]\n",
    "        \n",
    "        df_bids = df_bids.sort_values(by=\"P\", ascending=False)\n",
    "        # Note that when y is negative, the buy side of the orderbook will be used (since liq. demanders want to sell)\n",
    "        df_bids['tot_y'] = -df_bids['Q'].cumsum()\n",
    "        #print(df_bids)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Now ask side\n",
    "        df_asks = df[df['S'] == 'S']\n",
    "        df_asks = df_asks.sort_values(by=\"P\", ascending=True)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        df_asks['tot_y'] = df_asks['Q'].cumsum()\n",
    "        self.df = pd.concat([df_bids, df_asks], axis=0)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        self.df['y'] = self.df['tot_y']\n",
    "        self.df = self.df.drop('tot_y', axis=1)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        self.percentile = 0.99\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def get_range(self):\n",
    "        '''Finds a reasonable range of prices for estimating the orderbook'''\n",
    "        bb = self.df[self.df['S']=='B']['P'].max()\n",
    "        ba = self.df[self.df['S']=='S']['P'].min()\n",
    "        midpoint = (bb + ba)/2\n",
    "        bid_cutoff = -self.df[self.df['S']=='B']['y'].min()*self.percentile\n",
    "        ask_cutoff = self.df[self.df['S']=='S']['y'].max()*self.percentile\n",
    "        #print(-bid_cutoff, ask_cutoff)\n",
    "        bids = self.df[(self.df['S']=='B') & (self.df['y'] > -bid_cutoff)]\n",
    "        asks = self.df[(self.df['S']=='S') & (self.df['y'] < ask_cutoff)]\n",
    "        df_temp = pd.concat([bids, asks])\n",
    "        df_temp = df_temp.sort_values('P')\n",
    "        lower = df_temp['P'].min()\n",
    "        upper = df_temp['P'].max()\n",
    "        return (lower, upper)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def get_bbo(self):\n",
    "        '''Returns the best bid and best offer in a tuple (best_bid, best_offer)'''\n",
    "        bb = self.df[self.df['S']=='B']['P'].max()\n",
    "        ba = self.df[self.df['S']=='S']['P'].min()\n",
    "        return (bb, ba)\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def get_midpoint(self):\n",
    "        '''Returns the midpoint of the best bid and best offer'''\n",
    "        bb = self.df[self.df['S']=='B']['P'].max()\n",
    "        ba = self.df[self.df['S']=='S']['P'].min()\n",
    "        mp = (bb + ba)/2\n",
    "        return mp\n",
    "\n",
    "    def estimate_ols(self, lower, upper):\n",
    "        '''Estimate the slope of the orderbook using prices between lower and upper.'''\n",
    "        df = self.df[(self.df['P'] >= lower) & (self.df['P'] <= upper)]\n",
    "        df = df.sort_values([\"P\"])\n",
    "        model = sm.ols(formula='y ~ P', data=df).fit()\n",
    "        #print(model.summary())\n",
    "        return model\n",
    "        \n",
    "        \n",
    "    def parameter_estimates(self, lower, upper):\n",
    "        '''Estimates the parameters p_{0}, and 2\\sigma_{u}/\\sqrt{\\Sigma_{0}} using OLS'''\n",
    "        est = self.estimate_ols(lower,upper)\n",
    "        #pprint(est.params)\n",
    "        p_0 = -est.params['Intercept']/est.params['P']\n",
    "        #pprint(p_0)\n",
    "        noise_to_signal = 0.5*est.params['P']\n",
    "        return {'p': p_0, 'ratio': noise_to_signal}\n",
    "        \n",
    "        \n",
    "            \n",
    "    def plot(self, lower, upper):\n",
    "        '''Plot the orderbook between prices lower and upper.'''\n",
    "        df = self.df[(self.df['P'] >= lower) & (self.df['P'] <= upper)]\n",
    "        df = df.sort_values([\"P\"])\n",
    "        plt.plot(df['P'], df['y'])\n",
    "        plt.show()\n",
    "        plt.close()\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def plot_estimates(self, lower, upper):\n",
    "        '''Plots the orderbook between lower and upper as well as the estimates of the orderbook'''\n",
    "        df = self.df[(self.df['P'] >= lower) & (self.df['P'] <= upper)]\n",
    "        df = df.sort_values([\"P\"])\n",

    "        plt.plot(pvec, yvec)\n",
    "        plt.show()\n",
    "        plt.close()\n",

    "class OrderBookSet(object):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __init__(self, ob_list):\n",

    "        \n",
    "    def plot_noise_ratio(self, title):\n",
    "        '''Plots the noise ratio over time for each OrderBook in the OrderBookSet'''\n",
    "        ts = []\n",
    "        rat = []\n",
    "        for ob in self.ob_list:\n",
    "            ts.append(ob.timestamp)\n",
    "            ra = ob.get_range()\n",
    "            rat.append(ob.parameter_estimates(*ra)['ratio'])\n",
    "            \n",
    "        plt.plot(ts, rat)\n",
    "        plt.xlabel(\"Seconds since midnight\")\n",
    "        plt.ylabel(\"$\\sigma_{u}/\\sqrt{\\Sigma_{0}}$\")\n",
    "        plt.title(title)\n",
    "        plt.show()\n",
    "        plt.close()\n",
    "        \n",
    "    def price_slope_correlation(self):\n",
    "        '''Returns the between the midpoint of the price and the slope of the orderbook'''\n",
    "        mp = []\n",
    "        rat = []\n",
    "        for ob in self.ob_list:\n",
    "            ra = ob.get_range()\n",
    "            rat.append(ob.parameter_estimates(*ra)['ratio'])\n",
    "            mp.append(ob.get_midpoint())\n",
    "            \n",
    "        mpa = np.array(mp)\n",
    "        rata = np.array(rat)\n",
    "        return np.corrcoef(mpa, rata)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def get_noise_ratio(self):\n",
